aks.  \n2. Disconnect / recycle Web Audio nodes in PrecisionClock.scheduleCallback to avoid accumulating nodes and CPU load.  \n3. Rework Scheduler to reuse a shared PrecisionClock (or accept one via DI) to prevent exceeding browser AudioContext limits and to keep all subsystems on a single time base.\n\n• Positive aspects  \n– Excellent TypeScript strict-mode compliance and descriptive JSDoc comments.  \n– Clear separation of concerns between timing, scheduling, and device layers.  \n– Comprehensive benchmark and drift-detection utilities demonstrate commitment to empirical validation.",
